  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220&deg;C/ 200&deg;C (fan)/ 425&deg;F/ Gas 7</p>\r\n<p>Dice the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on)&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>diced potatoes</strong> to one side of a baking tray, drizzle them with&nbsp;<strong>olive</strong>&nbsp;<strong>oil&nbsp;</strong>and season them generously with <strong>salt </strong></p>\r\n<p>Put the tray&nbsp;in the oven for 30 min or until the potatoes are cooked through and crispy</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, drain the&nbsp;<strong>cooked&nbsp;beetroot</strong>&nbsp;and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>\r\n<p>Dice the<strong> cooked&nbsp;beetroot</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Remove the&nbsp;baking tray from the oven and add the<strong> chopped beetroot</strong> to&nbsp;the other side of the tray</p>\r\n<p>Drizzle the <strong>beetroot</strong> with <strong>olive&nbsp;oil</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Return the tray to the oven for the remaining cooking time&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, grate the <strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (skins on)</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>fennel seeds</strong> to a&nbsp;<strong>pestle and mortar</strong> and grind them to a powder</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>pork mince</strong>,&nbsp;<strong>ground fennel seeds</strong>, <strong>grated apple</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a large bowl and give everything a good mix up</p>\r\n<p>Divide the <strong>pork mixture</strong> into 8 <span class=\"text-danger\">[16]</span> and shape into meatballs - these are your <strong>apple&nbsp;&amp;&nbsp;fennel meatballs</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/1038.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove the<strong> potato</strong> and <strong>beetroot</strong> tray from the oven and add the<strong> apple &amp; fennel meatballs&nbsp;</strong>to the potatoes</p>\r\n<p>Return the tray to the oven and cook for the remaining cooking time (approx. a further 20 min) or until the <strong>meatballs</strong> are browned and cooked through&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
